<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="655" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d655">
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Montreal</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-03">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 3, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>La délégation Franchise, a la suite de 1’inauguration du monument
                            Champlain et au moment ou elle quitte le sol des États-Unis, exprime au
                            President de la grande République soeur l’hommage de sa gratitude et de
                            son respect.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanotaux.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>